Base:Descriptions.Base:Description: shadowy stone basement

A large, shadowy basement with a high ceiling. The room is hazy with smoke, and you catch the strong scent of sour alcohol. The walls are of dark stone braced by oak beams, except for the north wall which is made entirely of large stacked stones. A white line is painted on the floor in the southern side of the room. In the center of the room is a round card table surrounded by chairs. Along the north wall is a rectangular table meant for dicing. A wooden bench rests against the east wall. In the southwest corner of the room is a stack of kegs.

some rusty grating leading down
A square iron grating is inset into the floor near the middle of the west wall. It is rusty and scratched, and roughly 3 feet by 3 feet in size.
A rusty square grating in the west side of the floor.
You slowly lower the grating closed. It shudders and shrieks painfully before slamming into place in a cloud of rust.
You arrive from the grating in the floor and climb out of the hole.
You crawl into the hole in the floor and descend a ladder into the darkness below.
You wrap your fingers around the grating and yank it upward. The neglected hinges shriek in protest and rust flakes off as it opens.

bench

This bench was fancy once. The finely stained chestnut wood has grown faded over the years. The ends of the bench, which are wrought of iron in cunning shapes, must have looked beautiful, but now that the gold paint is peeling off, it just looks tacky. The wood is soft and well-contoured, however, and is very comfortable.
A comfortable bench made of faded chestnut wood and iron gilded with peeling gold paint.
the ceiling

Thick, dark wooden joists, sturdy and straight, cross rough oak planks of various widths. The planks are very carefully laid so that they fit together almost seamlessly. Cobwebs hang like rotting silk from thick wooden beams. A trapdoor can be easily seen in the ceiling.
There seems to be a ceiling overhead in this dark room, supported by thick wooden beams.

the cobwebs
Cobwebs hang from the ceiling, the upper walls and dust the corners of the room. These dusty icicles hang mournfully like the tattered wisps of a death shroud.

bundle of darts
A bundle of slender darts, pointed at one end and feathered at the other. They are designed to be propelled by the hand at the target's bullseye.
A bundle of slender darts, pointed at one end and feathered at the other.
the floor

The patchwork stone floor is crafted of rough, uneven, flat stones of various shapes, sizes, and colors. The stones are crudely fitted together, with smaller stones wedged between the larger ones to form a somewhat consistent surface. Some of the stones even seem to sparkle in the bright light. On the southern end of the floor is a painted white line. A rusty grate is inset into the floor near the middle of the west wall.
The patchwork stone floor is crafted of rough, uneven, flat stones.

the eastern wall

The close-studded, half-timbered eastern wall is constructed of dark, unpainted oak posts (the studs) and a few diagonal arch-braces, joined with mortises and pegs, and all somewhat less than perfectly flat and square. Few of the studs are of the same width, and some have slight curves or uneven surfaces. The arch-braces rise from some of the larger posts, and curve slightly 'inward' as they rise to support the ceiling beams. Between the wooden posts and braces are stacks of rough, dark stone, mortared together. These stones are recessed about half an inch beyond the surrounding wooden framing.
